fields.name: VCO_MUX

fields.name: OSCout_MUX
fields.description: Select the source for OSCout

fields.name: OSCout_FMT
fields.description: Selects the output format of OSCout. When powered down, these pins may be used as CLKin2.

fields.name: SYSREF_CLKin0_MUX
fields.description: Selects the SYSREF output from SYSREF_MUX or CLKin0 direct

fields.name: SYSREF_DIV[12:8]
fields.description: SYSREF Divider MSBs

fields.name: SYSREF_DIV[7:0]
fields.description: SYSREF Divider LSBs

fields.name: SYSREF_DDLY[12:8]
fields.description: These registers set the delay of the SYSREF digital delay value. MSBs

fields.name: SYSREF_DDLY[7:0]
fields.description: These registers set the delay of the SYSREF digital delay value. LSBs

fields.name: SYSREF_PULSE_CNT
fields.description: Sets the number of SYSREF pulses generated when not in continuous mode. See SYSREF_CLKin0_MUX, SYSREF_MUX for more information on SYSREF modes.

fields.name: PLL2_NCLK_MUX
fields.description: Selects the input to the PLL2 N divider

fields.name: PLL1_NCLK_MUX
fields.description: Selects the input to the PLL1 N delay

fields.name: FB_MUX
fields.description: When in zero-delay mode, the feedback mux selects the clock output to be fed back into the PLL1 N divider.

fields.name: FB_MUX_EN
fields.description: When using zero-delay, FB_MUX_EN must be set to 1 to power up the feedback mux

fields.name: PLL1_PD
fields.description: Powerdown PLL1

fields.name: VCO_LDO_PD
fields.description: Powerdown VCO_LDO

fields.name: VCO_PD
fields.description: Powerdown VCO

fields.name: OSCin_PD
fields.description: Powerdown the OSCin port

fields.name: SYSREF_GBL_PD
fields.description: Powerdown individual SYSREF outputs depending on the setting of SDCLKoutY_DIS_MODE for each SYSREF output. SYSREF_GBL_PD allows many SYSREF outputs to be controlled through a single bit.

fields.name: SYSREF_PD
fields.description: Powerdown the SYSREF circuitry and divider. If powered down, SYSREF output mode cannot be used. SYNC cannot be provided either.

fields.name: SYSREF_DDLY_PD
fields.description: Powerdown the SYSREF digital delay circuitry

fields.name: SYSREF_PLSR_PD
fields.description: Powerdown the SYSREF pulse generator.

fields.name: DDLYd_SYSREF_EN
fields.description: Enables dynamic digital delay on SYSREF outputs

fields.name: DDLYd12_EN
fields.description: Enables dynamic digital delay on DCLKout12

fields.name: DDLYd10_EN
fields.description: Enables dynamic digital delay on DCLKout10

fields.name: DDLYd7_EN
fields.description: Enables dynamic digital delay on DCLKout8

fields.description: Enables dynamic digital delay on DCLKout6

fields.name: DDLYd4_EN
fields.description: Enables dynamic digital delay on DCLKout4

fields.name: DDLYd2_EN
fields.description: Enables dynamic digital delay on DCLKout2

fields.name: DDLYd0_EN
fields.description: Enables dynamic digital delay on DCLKout0

fields.name: DDLYd_STEP_CNT
fields.description: Sets the number of dynamic digital delay adjustments that occur.

fields.name: SYSREF_CLR
fields.description: Resets and arms the SDCLKoutY_DDLY path, allowing local digital delays to take effect after a SYNC event. Except during the SYSREF setup procedure (see SYNC/SYSREF), this bit should always be programmed to 0. While this bit is set, extra current is used. Refer to Table 87.

fields.name: SYNC_1SHOT_EN
fields.description: SYNC one shot enables edge-sensitive SYNC.

values.name: LEVEL_DETECTION
values.description: SYNC is level sensitive and outputs are held in SYNC while SYNC is asserted.

values.name: EDGE_DETECTION
values.description: SYNC is edge sensitive, outputs are SYNCed on rising edge of SYNC. This results in the clock being held in SYNC for a minimum amount of time.

fields.name: SYNC_POL
fields.description: Sets the polarity of the SYNC pin.

fields.name: SYNC_EN
fields.description: Enables the SYNC functionality.

fields.name: SYNC_PLL2_DLD
fields.description: Assert SYNC until PLL2 DLD = 1

fields.name: SYNC_PLL1_DLD
fields.description: Assert SYNC until PLL1 DLD = 1

fields.name: SYNC_MODE
fields.description: Sets the method of generating a SYNC event.

values.name: NO_DLD_FLAGS_NO_SYNC
values.description: Prevents SYNC pin, SYNC_PLL1_DLD flag, or SYNC_PLL2_DLD flag from generating a SYNC event.

values.name: SYNC_FROM_PIN_OR_DLD_FLAG
values.description: SYNC event generated from SYNC pin or, if enabled, the SYNC_PLL1_DLD flag or SYNC_PLL2_DLD flag

values.name: SYNC_PULSER_OR_PIN_OR_DLD_FLAG
values.description: For use with pulser  SYNC/SYSREF pulses are generated by pulser block through the SYNC pin or, if enabled, the SYNC_PLL1_DLD flag or SYNC_PLL2_DLD flag.

values.name: SYNC_WHEN_REGISTER_UPDATED
values.description: For use with pulser  SYNC/SYSREF pulses are generated by pulser block when programming register 0x13E (SYSREF_PULSE_CNT) is written to (see SYSREF Pulser).

fields.name: SYNC_DISSYSREF
fields.description: Prevents the SYSREF clocks from becoming synchronized during a SYNC event. If SYNC_DISSYSREF is enabled, it continues to operate normally during a SYNC event.

fields.name: SYNC_DIS12
fields.description: Prevents the device clock output from becoming synchronized during a SYNC event or SYSREF clock. If SYNC_DIS bit for a particular output is enabled, then it continues to operate normally during a SYNC event or SYSREF clock.

fields.name: CLKin2_EN
fields.description: Enable CLKin2 to be used during auto-switching of CLKin_SEL_MODE.

fields.name: CLKin1_EN
fields.description: Enable CLKin1 to be used during auto-switching of CLKin_SEL_MODE.

fields.name: CLKin0_EN
fields.description: Enable CLKin0 to be used during auto-switching of CLKin_SEL_MODE.

fields.name: CLKin2_TYPE
fields.description: There are two buffer types for CLKin0, 1, and 2: bipolar and CMOS. Bipolar is recommended for differential inputs such as LVDS or LVPECL. CMOS is recommended for DC-coupled single-ended inputs. When using bipolar, CLKinX and CLKinX* must be AC coupled. When using CMOS, CLKinX and CLKinX* may be AC or DC coupled if the input signal is differential. If the input signal is single-ended, the used input may be either AC or DC coupled, and the unused input must AC grounded (see Driving CLKin and OSCin Pins With a SingleEnded Source).

fields.name: CLKin1_TYPE
fields.description: There are two buffer types for CLKin0, 1, and 2: bipolar and CMOS. Bipolar is recommended for differential inputs such as LVDS or LVPECL. CMOS is recommended for DC-coupled single-ended inputs. When using bipolar, CLKinX and CLKinX* must be AC coupled. When using CMOS, CLKinX and CLKinX* may be AC or DC coupled if the input signal is differential. If the input signal is single-ended, the used input may be either AC or DC coupled, and the unused input must AC grounded (see Driving CLKin and OSCin Pins With a SingleEnded Source).

fields.name: CLKin0_TYPE
fields.description: There are two buffer types for CLKin0, 1, and 2: bipolar and CMOS. Bipolar is recommended for differential inputs such as LVDS or LVPECL. CMOS is recommended for DC-coupled single-ended inputs. When using bipolar, CLKinX and CLKinX* must be AC coupled. When using CMOS, CLKinX and CLKinX* may be AC or DC coupled if the input signal is differential. If the input signal is single-ended, the used input may be either AC or DC coupled, and the unused input must AC grounded (see Driving CLKin and OSCin Pins With a SingleEnded Source).

fields.name: CLKin_SEL_POL
fields.description: Inverts the CLKin polarity for use in pin select mode.

fields.name: CLKin_SEL_MODE
fields.description: Sets the mode used in determining the reference for PLL1.

fields.name: CLKin1_OUT_MUX
fields.description: Selects where the output of the CLKin1 buffer is directed.

fields.name: CLKin0_OUT_MUX
fields.description: Selects where the output of the CLKin0 buffer is directed.

fields.name: CLKin_SEL0_MUX
fields.description: This set the output value of the CLKin_SEL0 pin. This register only applies if CLKin_SEL0_TYPE is set to an output mode

fields.name: CLKin_SEL0_TYPE
fields.description: This sets the I/O type of the CLKin_SEL0 pin.

fields.name: SDIO_RDBK_TYPE
fields.description: Sets the SDIO pin to open drain when during SPI readback in 3-wire mode.

fields.name: CLKin_SEL1_MUX
fields.description: This set the output value of the CLKin_SEL1 pin. This register only applies if CLKin_SEL1_TYPE is set to an output mode.

fields.name: CLKin_SEL1_TYPE
fields.description: This sets the I/O type of the CLKin_SEL1 pin.

fields.name: RESET_MUX
fields.description: This sets the output value of the RESET pin. This register only applies if RESET_TYPE is set to an output mode.

fields.name: RESET_TYPE
fields.description: This sets the I/O type of the RESET pin

fields.name: LOS_TIMEOUT
fields.description: This controls the amount of time in which no activity on a CLKin forces a clock switch event.

fields.name: LOS_EN
fields.description: Enables the LOS (loss-of-signal) timeout control. Valid only for MOS clock inputs. To ensure LOS is valid for AC-coupled inputs, no termination is allowed between CLKinX and CLKinX* pins unless DC-blocked. For example, 100- termination across CLKin0 and CLKin0* pins on the IC side of AC coupling capacitors would invalidate the LOS detector. If termination is required, it should be placed on the other side of the AC coupling capacitors, away from the IC pins

fields.name: TRACK_EN
fields.description: Enable the DAC to track the PLL1 tuning voltage, optionally for use in holdover mode. After device reset, tracking starts at DAC code = 512 (midrange). Tracking can be used to monitor PLL1 voltage in any mode.

values.name: ENABLED
values.description: Enabled, only tracks when PLL1 is locked.

fields.name: HOLDOVER_FORCE
fields.description: This bit forces holdover mode. When holdover mode is forced, if MAN_DAC_EN = 1, then the DAC sets the programmed MAN_DAC value. Otherwise the tracked DAC value sets the DAC voltage

fields.name: MAN_DAC_EN
fields.description: This bit enables the manual DAC mode.

fields.name: MAN_DAC[9:8]
fields.description: Sets the value of the manual DAC when in manual DAC mode. MSBs

fields.name: MAN_DAC[7:0]
fields.description: Sets the value of the manual DAC when in manual DAC mode. LSBs

fields.name: DAC_TRIP_LOW
fields.description: Voltage from GND at which holdover is entered if HOLDOVER_VTUNE_DET is enabled. Vtrip = (x + 1) * Vcc / 64

fields.name: DAC_CLK_MULT
fields.description: This is the multiplier for the DAC_CLK_CNTR which sets the rate at which the DAC value is tracked.

fields.name: DAC_TRIP_HIGH
fields.description: Voltage from Vcc at which holdover is entered if HOLDOVER_VTUNE_DET is enabled. Vtrip = (x + 1) * Vcc / 64

fields.name: DAC_CLK_CNTR
fields.description: This with DAC_CLK_MULT set the rate at which the DAC is updated. The update rate (in seconds) is = DAC_CLK_MULT * DAC_CLK_CNTR / PLL1 PDF (Hz)

fields.name: CLKin_OVERRIDE
fields.description: When CLKin_SEL_MODE = 0/1/2 to select a manual clock input, CLKin_OVERRIDE = 1 forces that clock input. Used with clock distribution mode for best performance.

values.name: OVERRIDE
values.description: Force select of only CLKin0/1/2, as specified by CLKin_SEL_MODE in manual mode

fields.name: HOLDOVER_PLL1_DET
fields.description: This enables the HOLDOVER when PLL1 lock detect signal transitions from high to low

values.name: PLL1_DLD_STICKY
values.description: PLL1 DLD does not cause a clock switch event

values.name: PLL1_DLD_SWITCH
values.description: PLL1 DLD causes a clock switch event

fields.name: HOLDOVER_LOS_DET
fields.description: This enables HOLDOVER when PLL1 LOS signal is detected.

fields.name: HOLDOVER_VTUNE_DET
fields.description: Enables the DAC Vtune rail detections. When the DAC achieves a specified Vtune, if this bit is enabled, the current clock input is considered invalid and an input clock switch event is generated.

fields.name: HOLDOVER_HITLESS_SWITCH
fields.description: Determines whether a clock switch event will enter holdover use hitless switching

values.name: HITLESS_SWITCH
values.description: Hitless switching (has an undefined switch time)

fields.name: HOLDOVER_EN
fields.description: Sets whether holdover mode can be entered when holdover conditions are met.

fields.name: HOLDOVER_DLD_CNT[13:8]
fields.description: The number of valid clocks of PLL1 PDF before holdover mode is exited. MSBs

fields.name: HOLDOVER_DLD_CNT[7:0]
fields.description: The number of valid clocks of PLL1 PDF before holdover mode is exited. LSBs

fields.name: CLKin0_R[13:8]
fields.description: The value of PLL1 R divider when CLKin0 is selected. MSBs

fields.name: CLKin0_R[7:0]
fields.description: The value of PLL1 R divider when CLKin0 is selected. LSBs

fields.name: CLKin1_R[13:8]
fields.description: The value of PLL1 R divider when CLKin1 is selected. MSBs

fields.name: CLKin1_R[7:0]
fields.description: The value of PLL1 R divider when CLKin1 is selected. LSBs

fields.name: CLKin2_R[13:8]
fields.description: The value of PLL1 R divider when CLKin2 is selected. MSBs

fields.name: CLKin2_R[7:0]
fields.description: The value of PLL1 R divider when CLKin2 is selected. LSBs

fields.name: PLL1_N[13:8]
fields.description: The value of PLL1 N divider. MSBs

fields.name: PLL1_N[7:0]
fields.description: The value of PLL1 N divider. LSBs

fields.name: PLL1_WND_SIZE
fields.description: PLL1_WND_SIZE sets the window size used for digital lock detect for PLL1. If the phase error between the reference and feedback of PLL1 is less than specified time, the PLL1 lock counter increments.

fields.name: PLL1_CP_TRI
fields.description: This bit allows for the PLL1 charge pump output pin, CPout1, to be placed into TRI-STATE.

fields.name: PLL1_CP_POL
fields.description: PLL1_CP_POL sets the charge pump polarity for PLL1. Many VCXOs use positive slope. A positive-slope VCXO increases output frequency with increasing voltage. A negativeslope VCXO decreases output frequency with increasing voltage.

fields.name: PLL1_CP_GAIN
fields.description: This field programs the PLL1 charge pump output current level. Iout = 50 A + x * 100 A

fields.name: PLL1_DLD_CNT[13:8]
fields.description: The reference and feedback of PLL1 must be within the window of phase error, as specified by PLL1_WND_SIZE for this many phase detector cycles, before PLL1 digital lock detect is asserted. MSBs

fields.name: PLL1_DLD_CNT[7:0]

fields.name: OSCin_FREQ
fields.description: The frequency of the PLL2 reference input to the PLL2 phase detector (OSCin/OSCin* port) must be programmed to support proper operation of the frequency calibration routine, which locks the internal VCO to the target frequency.

fields.name: PLL2_XTAL_EN
fields.description: If an external crystal is being used to implement a discrete VCXO, the internal feedback amplifier must be enabled with this bit to complete the oscillator circuit.

fields.name: PLL2_REF_2X_EN
fields.description: Enabling the PLL2 reference frequency doubler allows for higher phase-detector frequencies on PLL2 than would normally be allowed with the given VCXO or crystal frequency. Higher phase-detector frequencies reduce the PLL N values, which makes the design of wider-loop bandwidth filters possible.

fields.name: PLL2_N_CAL[17:16]
fields.description: PLL2 never uses zero-delay during frequency calibration. These registers contain the value of the PLL2 N divider used with the PLL2 prescaler during calibration for cascaded zero-delay mode. When calibration is complete, PLL2 uses the PLL2_N value. Cascaded zero-delay mode occurs when PLL2_NCLK_MUX = 1. MSBs

fields.name: PLL2_N_CAL[15:8]
fields.description: PLL2 never uses zero-delay during frequency calibration. These registers contain the value of the PLL2 N divider used with the PLL2 prescaler during calibration for cascaded zero-delay mode. When calibration is complete, PLL2 uses the PLL2_N value. fields.name: PLL2_WND_SIZE
fields.description: PLL2_WND_SIZE sets the window size used for digital lock detect for PLL2. If the phase error between the reference and feedback of PLL2 is less than the specified time, then the PLL2 lock counter increments. This value must be programmed to 2 (3.7 ns).

fields.name: PLL2_CP_GAIN
fields.description: This bit programs the PLL2 charge pump output current level. The table below also illustrates the impact of the PLL2 TRISTATE bit in conjunction with PLL2_CP_GAIN.

fields.name: PLL2_CP_POL
fields.description: PLL2_CP_POL sets the charge pump polarity for PLL2. The internal VCO requires the negative charge pump polarity to be selected. Many VCOs use positive slope. A positive-slope VCO increases output frequency with increasing voltage. A negative-slope VCO decreases output frequency with increasing voltage.

fields.name: PLL2_CP_TRI
fields.description: PLL2_CP_TRI TRI-STATEs the output of the PLL2 charge pump.

fields.name: SYSREF_REQ_EN
fields.description: Enables the SYNC/SYSREF_REQ pin to force the SYSREF_MUX = 3 for continuous pulses. When using this feature, enable the pulser and set SYSREF_MUX = 2 (pulser).

fields.name: PLL2_DLD_CNT[15:8]
